John E. McGlade - Wikipedia





















 






John E. McGlade

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

John E. McGlade (born 1954) is an American businessman.[1] He is the former Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President of Air Products & Chemicals.[1][2][3][4]



Contents


1 Biography

1.1 Early life
1.2 Career


2 References



Biography[edit]
Early life[edit]
John McGlade was born in 1954 in Bethlehem, Pennsylvania.[2] He received a Bachelor of Science in Industrial Engineering in 1976 and an M.B.A. in 1980, both from Lehigh University.[1][2][4]
Career[edit]
He joined Air Products & Chemicals in 1976.[2][3] He became President and Chief Executive Officer in October 2007, and Chairman of the Board in April 2008.[1][2]
He sits on the Board of Directors of the Goodyear Tire and Rubber Company, the American Chemistry Council, and the Executive Committee of the Council on Competitiveness.[2][3] He is a member of the American Society of Chemical Industry.[4] He sits on the Board of Trustees of his alma mater, Lehigh University.[2][4]
In 2012, he earned US$11.36 million.[1]
References[edit]


^ a b c d e Forbes 2012
^ a b c d e f g Air Products & Chemicals Board of Directors Archived 2014-04-28 at the Wayback Machine.
^ a b c Goodyear Tire and Rubber Company Board of Directors
^ a b c d Lehigh University Board of Trustees






 
